===subject:Reply to Veronica
===from:B. Kornegay
===date:Sun Oct 26  1:25:40 2003
===message:Veronica, I never even noticed that empty plate.  I read your reply and reviewed the picture.  I agree that it well represents “a period of great need and hardships”.  During the Great Depression, this is what the majority of Americans experienced.  It seemed unbelievable after all the prosperity of the 1920s.  My grandmother would talk of that time and how hard it was for a poor, rural black family trying to work a farm. She said they ate almost anything and learned how to search the wood for things that could be eaten. Many Black farmers started out in debt, trying to farm in poor soil with bad farm equipment and were hit extremely hard during the Great Depression.  They had to deal with being poor and with being discriminated against. 
=========yorg=========
